      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: centrifugal VAD hemolysis domain",
      "description": "The CFD model is applicable only to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry operating in continuous-flow VAD mode with Newtonian blood analogue fluid properties (hematocrit 40±3%). The hemolysis power-law constitutive model is calibrated for shear rates in the range 10–10000 s⁻¹ and exposure times 1–500 ms. The model is not applicable to pulsatile-flow VAD modes, non-Newtonian blood rheology regimes, or pump geometries with tip clearance deviating more than ±0.05 mm from the FDA reference geometry."
    },
